    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Lord, in me is all self-love, envy, anxiety"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Lord, in me is only pride and no humility."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I’m not pure, Lord, or trusting, neither absolute"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For Your purpose, I waver — I’m not resolute!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But dearest Lord, You’re all these things, all virtue’s in You,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "So Lord I lay my hands on You in all I do."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Such a laying on of hands is not for substitution;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When we lay our hands on Christ, it brings in a union."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "By our laying our hands on Christ, we are joined to Him."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "We become one — no longer two — we become Him!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In such a union all our weaknesses, wounds, and scars"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Are taken on by Him and His virtues become ours."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Such a union requires exercise through proper prayer"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "We open our failures, defects for our Lord to bear."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As we pray in this way, Christ — the One with no such sin"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As the life-giving Spirit moves and works within"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To live in us a life, a repetition of Christ our King,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The One who lived on earth the life of the burnt offering."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Lord, You’re balanced, fine and pure and loving through and through"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You welcome the leprous ones, blind, lame all come to You."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You have eyes of a dove, Lord — blemish free are You."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "No mixed motives, self-glory, what the Father says You do!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Your humility’s unsurpassed — obedient e’en unto death."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Trusting in the Father’s will, living by Him breath by breath!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thus, I open up to You each failure, blemish, and spot."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I want You to know me, Lord, and know all that I’m not."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You’re my Husband, my strong One, I am just Your wife."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Bear my burdens, my loved One, give me Your wonderful life!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I take up this exchange, God Himself is what I’ve got."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You can bear all that I am, You can be all that I’m not!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "You can bear all that I am, You can be all that I’m not!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    }
  ],
